{"title_page": "Count Fleet Sprint Handicap", "text_new": "{{Infobox horseraces\n| class         = Grade III\n| horse race    = Count Fleet Sprint Handicap\n| image         =\n| caption       =\n| location      = [[Oaklawn Park Race Track]]<br>[[Hot Springs, Arkansas]],<br>[[United States]]\n| inaugurated   = 1974\n| race type     = [[Thoroughbred]] - [[Flat racing]]\n| website       = [http://www.oaklawn.com/ Oaklawn Jockey Club, Inc.]\n| distance      = 6 [[furlong]]s\n| surface       = Dirt\n| track         = Left-handed\n| qualification = Four-years-old & up\n| weight        = Assigned\n| purse         = $500,000 (2019)\n| bonuses       =\n}}\nThe '''Count Fleet Sprint Handicap''' is a [[Graded stakes race|Grade III]] American [[Thoroughbred horse race]] held annually in mid April at [[Oaklawn Park Race Track]] in [[Hot Springs, Arkansas]] for horses age four and older, and contested on dirt over the [[Sprint (horse racing)|sprint]] distance of six [[furlong]]s. Inaugurated in 1974,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pedigreequery.com/index.php?query_type=stakes&search_bar=stakes&field=view&id=4282|work=Thoroughbred Pedigreequery|title=COUNT FLEET SPRINT HANDICAP - OAKLAWN PARK, AR  UNITED STATES - Grade III|accessdate=13 April 2013}}</ref> the event currently offers a purse of [[United States dollar|US$]]500,000.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.oaklawn.com/uploads/pages/2019_media_guide_web_version.pdf |title=2019 Media Guide |publisher=Oaklawn Racing Casino Resort |date=2019-11-02\n|accessdate=2019-11-02}}</ref>\n\nThe race is named in honor of the 1943 [[United States Triple Crown of Thoroughbred Racing|United States Triple Crown]] champion, [[Count Fleet]].\n\nIn 2020, Whitmore became the first horse to win the Count Fleet Sprint Handicap three times.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.paulickreport.com/news/thoroughbred-racing/whitmore-rolls-to-third-count-fleet-sprint-handicap-victory/|title=Whitmore Rolls To Third Count Fleet Sprint Handicap Victory|date=2020-04-18|website=Horse Racing News {{!}} Paulick Report|language=en|access-date=2020-04-18}}</ref>\n\n==Records==\n'''Speed record:'''\n* 1:08.00 @ 6 [[furlong]]s - Bonapaw (2001)\n\n'''Most wins:'''\n* 3 - Whitmore (2017, 2018, 2020)\n*2 - [[Dave's Friend]] (1983, 1984)\n* 2 - Bordonaro (2006, 2007)\n* 2 - Semaphore Man (2008, 2009)\n\n'''Most wins by a [[jockey]]:'''\n* 5 - [[Ricardo Santana Jr. ]] (2013, 2014, 2017, 2018, 2019)\n\n'''Most wins by a [[Horse trainer|trainer]]:'''\n* 3 - [[Steve Asmussen]] (2013, 2014, 2019)\n* 3 - [[William Spawr]] (1986, 2006, 2007)\n\n'''Most wins by an owner:'''\n* 2 - Irene C. Udouj (1974, 1977)\n* 2 - [[John A. Franks|John Franks]] (1983, 1984)\n* 2 - Courtlandt Farm (2005, 2006)\n* 2 - Double Bogey Stable (2008, 2009)\n* 2 - Southern Springs Stables/R. V. LaPenta/Head of Plains Partners LLC (2017, 2018)\n\n==Winners==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"font-size:90%\"\n|- \n! style=\"width:30px\" | Year<br>\n! style=\"width:110px\" | Winner<br>\n! style=\"width:20px\" | Age<br>\n! style=\"width:110px\" | Jockey<br>\n! style=\"width:120px\" | Trainer<br>\n! Owner<br>\n! style=\"width:25px\" | Time<br>\n! style=\"width:25px\" | Win[[United States dollar|$]]\n|-\n|2020\n|Whitmore \n|7\n|[[Joseph Talamo]]\n|Ron Moquett \n|Southern Springs Stables/R. V. LaPenta/Head of Plains Partners LLC\n|1:08.95\n|$350,000\n|-\n|align=center|2019\n|[[Mitole]]\n|align=center|4\n|[[Ricardo Santana Jr.]]\n|[[Steve Asmussen]]\n|William L. & Corinne Heiligbrodt\n|align=center|1:09.36\n|align=center|$300,000\n|-\n|align=center|2018\n|Whitmore\n|align=center|5\n|Ricardo Santana Jr.\n|Ron Moquett\n|Southern Springs Stables/R. V. LaPenta/Head of Plains Partners LLC \n|align=center|1:09.77\n|align=center|$240,000\n|-\n|align=center|2017\n|Whitmore\n|align=center|4\n|Ricardo Santana Jr.\n|Ron Moquett\n|Southern Springs Stables/R. V. LaPenta/Head of Plains Partners LLC \n|align=center|1:08.35\n|align=center|$240,000\n|-\n|align=center|2016\n|Subtle Indian\n|